CatDescriptText: Cutline of images published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 25, 1941, pg. 17 reads: "Alphas Map Plans For Columbus Invasion - Frank Bolden, Talton McCullough and Morris Fountain, of the Alpha Phi Alpha basketball team, talk over a few important plays they hope to execute Friday night against the Columbus Alphas on the Centre Avenue Y court. The Columbus team will bring a number of former collegiate greats here, including Jesse Owens, the famous track star."
TitMainTitle: Alpha Phi Alpha basketball team members Frank Bolden, Talton McCullough, and Morris Fountain in Centre Avenue YMCA
